<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="2-costs-of-medical-sciences-and-health-programs-in-turkey">2. Costs of Medical Sciences and Health Programs in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey&#8217;s <strong>medical sciences education</strong> is much more affordable than in Western Europe and the US.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>State Universities:</strong> Annual tuition usually ranges from <strong>3,000 &#8211; 10,000 USD</strong>.</li>



<li><strong>Private Universities:</strong> Tuition fees are between <strong>10,000 &#8211; 25,000 USD</strong>, with many scholarships available.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Research Fellowships in Medical Sciences</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong><strong>TÜBİTAK and YÖK Support Programs:</strong> Turkey allocates large funds for scientific research.</strong></li>



<li><strong><strong>Turkey Scholarships:</strong> Offers full scholarship programs for international students.</strong></li>



<li><strong><strong>University Internal Scholarships:</strong> Students can receive financial support through merit-based scholarships.</strong></li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Also, the cost of living in Turkey is quite affordable compared to European countries. Students can receive a high quality education at low costs.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Scholarship Opportunities:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
