":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/international-relations-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/international-relations-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/international-relations-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/international-relations-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International relations is a broad academic field that brings together many different disciplines such as political science, economics, law and history. Studying in this department enables students to analyze global issues, develop diplomatic skills and pursue a career in international politics.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is a country with a strategic location and long-standing academic traditions in international relations education. So, what are the advantages of studying in this field in Turkey? Here are the details:</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="international-relations-education-in-turkey-advantages">International Relations Education in Turkey: Advantages</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="1-strategic-position-and-cultural-diversity">1. Strategic Position and Cultural Diversity</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is located at the crossroads of <strong>Europe, Asia and the Middle East</strong>, making it a unique place to study international relations. The country has strong diplomatic relations with both the West and the East, giving students the opportunity to understand different political and cultural perspectives.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Turkey has close relations with international organizations such as NATO, G20, Organization of Islamic Cooperation and the UN.</li>



<li>The EU candidacy process offers an important experience for students who want to understand European diplomacy.</li>



<li>Strong ties with the Middle East and the Caucasus create attractive opportunities for those wishing to specialize in regional politics and foreign relations.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Studying in Turkey is also a great advantage in terms of getting to know different cultures. Especially cities like Istanbul, Ankara and Izmir create a global educational atmosphere by hosting students from all over the world.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="2-high-quality-universities-and-international-accreditation">2. High Quality Universities and International Accreditation</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey has internationally ranked, accredited universities. Universities supervised by YÖK (Higher Education Council) provide world-class education.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Boğaziçi University and METU</strong> are the leading institutions in the field of international relations in the Times Higher Education and QS World University Rankings.</li>



<li><strong>Koç University and Sabancı University</strong> are among the globally recognized private universities that teach in English.</li>



<li><strong>Galatasaray University</strong> offers an integrated education with the French academic system, appealing to students who want to gain a European perspective.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some Turkish universities also offer students the opportunity to study abroad through <strong>Erasmus+ and exchange programs</strong>. This gives students studying international relations the chance to spend a semester or a year at universities in <strong>Europe, the USA and Asia</strong>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="3-economic-education-and-living-costs">3. Economic Education and Living Costs</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is much more affordable in terms of education and living costs for international students compared to Western Europe, North America and some Asian countries.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>The annual tuition fee</strong> at public universities typically ranges from <strong>US$500 to US$2,000</strong> for international students.</li>



<li><strong>Although annual fees</strong> at private universities typically range from <strong>US$5,000 to US$20,000</strong>, these costs can be reduced through various scholarship opportunities.</li>



<li><strong>Housing and living expenses</strong> range from <strong>US$400-800 per month</strong> in big cities like Istanbul, while in smaller cities it is possible to live more affordably.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Especially when compared to universities in Europe and the US, studying international relations in Turkey is a more affordable and accessible option.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="4-broad-scholarship-and-support-programs-for-international-students">4. Broad Scholarship and Support Programs for International Students</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey offers <strong>scholarship and financial support programs</strong> to thousands of international students every year.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Turkey Scholarships:</strong> These are full scholarship programs for foreign students. It includes accommodation, <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-health-insurance-options-in-turkey/" data-type="post" data-id="5520">health insurance</a> and monthly pocket money.</li>



<li><strong>University Scholarships:</strong> Many universities such as METU, Koç, Sabancı offer merit-based scholarships.</li>



<li><strong><strong>TUBITAK Research Scholarships:</strong> Provides financial support to international students who wish to conduct academic research in Turkey.</strong></li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Thanks to these scholarship programs, international students can significantly reduce the cost of their education and continue their studies in comfort.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="5-international-career-opportunities-and-internship-opportunities">5. International Career Opportunities and Internship Opportunities</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students who study international relations in Turkey can have job opportunities in many different fields such as <strong>diplomacy, international trade, media and academic career</strong>.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>The Ministry of Foreign Affairs</strong> is an important employer for international relations graduates. For students who want to become a diplomat in Turkey, you can check <a href="https://www.mfa.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">T.C. Ministry of Foreign Affairs&#8217; career page</a>.</li>



<li><strong>Organizations such as the United Nations (UN), the European Union (EU) and the World Bank</strong> are international organizations with offices in Turkey.</li>



<li><strong>Private sector and multinational companies</strong> have the opportunity to work in foreign relations, trade and media.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Also, many universities offer internship opportunities in international organizations. In particular, internships in organizations such as EU projects, UNESCO and NATO give students an advantage in the global job market.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


