<h2 id="sonuç-turkiyede-uluslararasi-iliskiler-okumumaya-deger-mi" class="wp-block-heading">Is International Relations in Turkey Worth Studying?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-heading">&lt;Studying international relations in Turkey is a great opportunity to gain a global perspective and build a strong career. With its wide range of academic options, scholarship opportunities and international career opportunities, Turkey is an attractive country for those who want to study in this field.</p>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📌 <strong>Want to choose the best university for you or inquire about scholarship applications? <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/" data-type="link" data-id="https://roadtostudy.com/"> Contact us!</a></strong></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">How many international relations departments are there in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This number varies according to different sources, but as of 2025, more than 80 universities have a Department of International Relations.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-there-a-job-opportunity-in-international-relations">Is there a job opportunity in international relations?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, there are. There are job opportunities in various fields such as diplomacy, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, international organizations, multinational corporations, media, banking and academia.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-tl-salary-does-international-relations-get">How much TL salary does international relations get?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Salaries increase according to experience: Experts with less than 1 year of experience receive an average salary of 32,300 TL, experts with 4-6 years of experience receive 49,600 TL, and experts with 15+ years of experience receive an average salary of 77,000 TL.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">In which university is the best international relations department in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Although rankings and preferences may vary, Bogazici University, Bilkent University and Galatasaray University are generally cited as the most prominent universities in this field.</p>



