Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/media-and-communication-programs-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/media-and-communication-programs-in-turkey.webp","width":"1168","height":"880","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/media-and-communication-programs-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/media-and-communication-programs-in-turkey/","name":"Media and Communication Programs in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2025-10-21T16:47:11+03:00","dateModified":"2025-10-21T17:47:09+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/media-and-communication-programs-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"articleSection":"University and Programs","headline":"Media and Communication Programs in Turkey","description":"Do you dream of a career in which digital media is ground-breaking, journalism is cutting edge, or advertising is a creative outlet? Then it&#039;s time to take a","keywords":"Media and Communication","@type":"Article","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"datePublished":"2025-10-21T16:47:11+03:00","dateModified":"2025-10-21T17:47:09+03:00","image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/media-and-communication-programs-in-turkey.webp"},"name":"Media and Communication Programs in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/media-and-communication-programs-in-turkey/#schema-32864","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/media-and-communication-programs-in-turkey/#webpage"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/media-and-communication-programs-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Do you dream of a career in which digital media is ground-breaking, journalism is cutting edge, or advertising is a creative outlet? Then it&#8217;s time to take a look at Turkey! The media industry is booming here and offers an education that is both affordable and full of opportunities for international students. From the bustling studios of Istanbul to the deep-rooted academic heritage of Ankara, there is a Media and Communication program in every city. So, what do media and communication programs in Turkey offer you? Let&#8217;s discover together!</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="best-media-and-communication-schools">Best Media and Communication Schools</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many quality universities in Turkey for those who want to study media and communication. Each focusing on different fields, these schools offer students strong academic programs, internship opportunities and hands-on training. So, which university stands out in which field? Here are the details!</p>


<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="1-istanbul-university-faculty-of-communication">1. Istanbul University &#8211; Faculty of Communication</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Location:</strong> Istanbul<br><strong>Foundation:</strong> 1950s<br><strong>Featured Fields:</strong> Journalism, Radio-TV, Public Relations</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Istanbul University is one of the oldest academic institutions in Turkey. With the education it offers in the field of media and communication, it has trained many successful journalists, televangelists and communication experts. The faculty has departments such as <strong>Radio, Television and Cinema, Public Relations and Publicity, Journalism</strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Featured Advantages:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>The university has its own television studio and radio station.</li>



<li>They have strong collaborations with TRT and private media organizations.</li>



<li>Istanbul is the media center of Istanbul, offering students a wide range of internship and job opportunities.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📌 <strong>For more information, please visit <a href="https://iletisim.istanbul.edu.tr/tr/_" data-type="link" data-id="https://iletisim.istanbul.edu.tr/tr/_" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Istanbul University</a> website.</strong></p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="2-ankara-university-faculty-of-communication">2. Ankara University &#8211; Faculty of Communication</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Location:</strong> Ankara<br><strong>Foundation:</strong> 1965<br><strong>Featured Fields:</strong> Journalism, Public Relations, Advertising</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ankara University is one of the pioneers of communication education in Turkey. It is known for its quality education in journalism, public relations and advertising. In addition to theoretical courses, students can also receive practical training here.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Featured Advantages:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>The university has its own student newspaper and radio station.</li>



<li>Provides internship opportunities with public institutions and media organizations.</li>



<li>Graduates usually work in national newspapers and television channels.</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="3-galatasaray-university-faculty-of-communication">3. Galatasaray University &#8211; Faculty of Communication</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Location:</strong> Istanbul<br><strong>Foundation:</strong> 1994<br><strong>Featured Areas:</strong> Digital Media, International Media, Advertising</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Galatasaray University is a prestigious French-language university. The faculty of media and communication has a particularly strong program in international media and digital communication.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Featured Advantages:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>You can make an advantageous entry into the international media sector by studying French.</li>



<li>Offers internship opportunities abroad, linked to media organizations in Europe.</li>



<li>There are innovative course programs in digital media and advertising.</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="4-bahcesehir-university-new-media-department">4. Bahçeşehir University &#8211; New Media Department</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Location:</strong> Istanbul<br><strong>Foundation:</strong> 1998<br><strong>Featured Areas:</strong> Digital Media, Social Media, Content Production</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bahçeşehir University has a modern and innovative approach to media and communication education. In particular, the <strong>New Media Department</strong> focuses on topics such as content production, social media management and <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-dijital-pazarlama-e-ticaret-kariyerleri/" data-type="post" data-id="8843">digital marketing</a> suitable for today&#8217;s digital world.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Featured Advantages:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Offers digital media-focused courses and hands-on training opportunities.</li>



<li><strong>CO-OP education model</strong> allows students to work in the media sector during their education.</li>



<li>You can gain international experience through overseas exchange programs.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📌 <strong>For more information, you can check the website of <a href="https://bau.edu.tr/icerik/3904-yeni-medya" data-type="link" data-id="https://bau.edu.tr/icerik/3904-yeni-medya" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bahçeşehir University New Media Department</a>.</strong></p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="5-bilgi-university-media-and-communication-department">5. Bilgi University &#8211; Media and Communication Department</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Location:</strong> Istanbul<br><strong>Foundation:</strong> 1996<br><strong>Featured Areas:</strong> Cinema-TV, Digital Media, Journalism</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Istanbul Bilgi University is a private university known for its hands-on media education. The faculty&#8217;s strong studio facilities give students a significant advantage in media and content production.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Featured Advantages:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>The university has its own television and radio studios.</li>



<li>Provides a strong academic program in digital media and creative content production.</li>



<li>It provides ideal training for those who want to produce content for Netflix, YouTube and other digital platforms.</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-to-consider-when-choosing-these-universities">What to consider when choosing these universities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are some important points that students who want to study media and communication in Turkey should pay attention to:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>The specialization of your department</strong>: Digital media, journalism or public relations? Determine which area you want to pursue.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Practical training opportunities</strong>: Consider internship opportunities, university media laboratories, radio-TV studios, etc.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>International opportunities</strong>: <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-erasmus-firsatlari/" data-type="post" data-id="2532">Gaining experience abroad through Erasmus and exchange programs</a> can be a great advantage.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Career paths of graduates</strong>: You can decide by researching where graduates of the university work in the media sector.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Scholarship and financial aid opportunities</strong>: Compare tuition fees and scholarship opportunities to find the most suitable option.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="media-and-communication-courses">Media and Communication Courses</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some of the basic courses offered in media departments are:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Media and Society</strong> &#8211; Social effects of media</li>



<li><strong>Journalism Techniques</strong> &#8211; News writing and interview</li>



<li><strong>Digital Media</strong> &#8211; Content production and social media management</li>



<li><strong>Advertising and Marketing</strong> &#8211; Campaign planning</li>



<li><strong>Film and Video Production</strong> &#8211; Camera techniques and editing</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="career-options-for-graduates">Career Options for Graduates</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many career options for media and communication graduates:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Journalist</strong> &#8211; News writing and interview</li>



<li><strong>Social Media Specialist</strong> &#8211; Digital marketing</li>



<li><strong>Advertiser</strong> &#8211; Creative campaign management</li>



<li><strong>Public Relations Specialist</strong> &#8211; Corporate Communication</li>



<li><strong>Film and Video Producer</strong> &#8211; YouTube, Netflix content</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The media sector in Turkey is growing rapidly and offers a wide range of jobs for graduates.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="advantages-of-media-education-in-turkey">Advantages of Media Education in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey offers many opportunities for students interested in a career in media and communication. Thanks to the universities&#8217; strong academic staff, connections with the media industry and international collaborations, students are able to combine theoretical and practical experience throughout their education. Here are the most important advantages of studying media and communication in Turkey:</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="broad-business-network-strong-connections-in-the-media-sector">Broad Business Network &#8211; Strong Connections in the Media Sector</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The media and communications sector has a wide business network and Turkey is one of the countries with a large market in this field. Especially big cities like Istanbul and Ankara are the center of media companies, television channels, newspapers, digital media platforms and advertising agencies.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Why is it important for students studying media in Turkey to be close to the business world?</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>The media sector has a rapidly developing and constantly renewing structure. Therefore, for students studying media, <strong>making direct connections with the industry</strong> offers great advantages in terms of career development.</li>



<li>University collaborations in the media sector provide students with a wide range of <strong>internship and job opportunities</strong>. Major media organizations such as <strong>CNN Türk, TRT, Fox TV, Hürriyet, Sabah, Anadolu Agency</strong> carry out joint projects with universities to recruit talented young people. Students through internship programs:</li>



<li>Learns news production processes,</li>



<li>Works with camera, editing and broadcast technologies,</li>



<li>Gains experience in television, digital media and print publishing.</li>



<li>The presence of graduates who have been successful in the sector offers students a strong <strong>alumni network</strong>. Many journalists, producers and editors working in the media in Turkey are graduates of media departments of universities. These alumni provide support to new graduates on their career journey, increasing job and internship opportunities.</li>



<li>Also, <strong>practical training</strong> plays a major role in media faculties. Thanks to live broadcasting studios, news rooms and media laboratories, students have the chance to turn theoretical knowledge into practice. In this way, the process of finding a job after graduation is accelerated and they adapt to the media sector faster.</li>



<li>As a result, it is of great importance for media students <strong>to be in close contact with the industry</strong> in order to shape their careers and establish a solid place for themselves in the professional world.</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="international-opportunities-erasmus-and-exchange-programs">International Opportunities &#8211; Erasmus and Exchange Programs</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Gaining international experience can be a great advantage for students studying media and communication in Turkey. Many universities offer students the chance to study or intern abroad through Erasmus+ and other international exchange programs.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong><strong>So what can Erasmus+ and exchange programs bring you?</strong></strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>The opportunity to get to know Europe&#8217;s media sector closely: Seeing the working systems of media organizations in Europe will make a great contribution to your career.</li>



<li>A multicultural educational experience: You gain a global perspective by working with students from different cultures.</li>



<li>Chance to make a difference in your CV: Studying abroad puts you one step ahead of your competitors in job applications.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Featured Universities:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Istanbul Bilgi University</strong> &#8211; Sends students to media schools in Europe through Erasmus.</li>



<li><strong>Ankara University</strong> &#8211; offers exchange programs with countries such as Germany, France and Spain.</li>



<li><strong>Galatasaray University</strong> &#8211; French-language university, particularly linked to media schools in France.</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="pratik-egitim-university-media-laboratories">Pratik Eğitim &#8211; University Media Laboratories</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Media and communication education is not just about theoretical courses. To get a good media education, hands-on training and sectoral experience are a must! Many universities in Turkey stand out with their media laboratories, radio and television studios, content production centers and digital media projects that offer students the opportunity to practice.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>The most important practical training opportunities for students:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Universities have their own television and radio channels</strong>: Istanbul University, Bilgi University and Bahçeşehir University have their own media production centers.</li>



<li><strong>Student projects</strong>: Universities organize workshops and events where media students can produce content.</li>



<li><strong>Content production labs</strong>: There are studios where you can practice new media and digital marketing.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Featured Universities:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Bilgi University</strong> &#8211; Provides students with practical experience through its media laboratories and film studios.</li>



<li><strong>Bahçeşehir University</strong> &#8211; New media department offers students hands-on training in digital content production and social media management.</li>



<li><strong>Istanbul University</strong> &#8211; There is a radio-television center that offers students hands-on broadcasting training.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Tip:</strong> If you want to work in media, make sure to take advantage of the hands-on training opportunities offered by your university and participate in student projects! </p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📌 <strong>Cost advantages of studying media in Turkey:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Low tuition fees at state universities</strong>: For example, annual tuition fees at public schools such as Istanbul University and Ankara University are very affordable.</li>



<li><strong>Scholarship opportunities at private universities</strong>: Foundation universities such as Bahçeşehir, Bilgi and Koç University offer various scholarships for media students.</li>



<li><strong>Living costs are lower than in Europe and the US</strong>: Even in big cities like Istanbul and Ankara, rent and living costs are much more affordable than in Western European cities.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Featured Universities:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Ankara University</strong> &#8211; As a public university, it offers low-cost education.</li>



<li><strong>Bahçeşehir University</strong> &#8211; Provides full and partial scholarship media programs for successful students.</li>



<li><strong>Istanbul Bilgi University</strong> &#8211; Offers a wide range of scholarships for media majors.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📌 <strong>You can visit <a href="https://www.yok.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YÖK Scholarship Programs</a> website for information about scholarships!</strong></p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="does-it-make-sense-to-read-media-in-turkey">Does it make sense to read media in Turkey?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are considering a career in media, journalism, advertising or digital content production, studying in Turkey could be a good option! </p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📌 <strong>Apply now!</strong> To enroll in media and communication programs in Turkey <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/" data-type="link" data-id="https://roadtostudy.com/">contact us.</a></p>



