e":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/language-and-literature-programs-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/language-and-literature-programs-in-turkey.webp","width":"1168","height":"880","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/language-and-literature-programs-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/language-and-literature-programs-in-turkey/","name":"Language and Literature Programs in Turkey","datePublished":"2025-10-24T14:45:45+03:00","dateModified":"2025-10-24T14:45:46+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/language-and-literature-programs-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Language and Literature Programs in Turkey","keywords":"Literature Programs in Turkey,Language and Literature Programs","datePublished":"2025-10-24T14:45:45+03:00","dateModified":"2025-10-24T14:45:46+03:00","articleSection":"University and Programs","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"In this article, we take a look at the best language and literature programs in Turkey, the application process and career opportunities after graduation.","name":"Language and Literature Programs in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/language-and-literature-programs-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/language-and-literature-programs-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/language-and-literature-programs-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/language-and-literature-programs-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Studying in Turkey offers great advantages for international students with its well-established universities, multilingual education options and affordable living conditions.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In this article, we take a look at the best language and literature programs in Turkey, the application process and career opportunities after graduation.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="why-you-should-study-language-and-literature-in-turkey">Why You Should Study Language and Literature in Turkey</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="rich-literary-and-cultural-heritage">Rich Literary and Cultural Heritage</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey has a great accumulation of language and literature as it is the intersection point of different civilizations. While studying <strong>language and literature</strong> in Turkey, you can find the opportunity to study both classical and contemporary works of literature.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey, with its thousands of years of history, <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-sanat-kultur-kariyer/" data-type="post" data-id="9104">multicultural character</a> and strong literary tradition, offers a unique academic environment for students who wish to study <strong>language and literature</strong>. <strong>Language and literature education in Turkey</strong> offers a broad perspective that covers not only Turkish literature, but also Ottoman, Persian, Arabic and Western literature.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="1-turkey-is-the-intersection-of-different-civilizations">1. Turkey is the Intersection of Different Civilizations</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is located in a strategic location where <strong>Europe, Asia and the Middle East converge</strong>. For this reason, Turkish literature has been influenced by Eastern and Western cultures throughout history and has a multifaceted structure.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/osmanlicadan-turkceye-dil-reformu-etkileri/" data-type="post" data-id="9154">A literary heritage intertwining Arabic, Persian and Turkish was formed during the Ottoman Empire</a>.</li>



<li>Modern Turkish literature, which developed under Western influence, has interacted with French, English and Russian literatures since the Tanzimat Period.</li>



<li>Republican and contemporary Turkish literature has gained a global identity by blending both traditional and contemporary narratives.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This multi-layered structure allows you to gain a broad perspective on both Eastern and Western literatures while studying language and literature in Turkey.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Example:</strong> While studying Ottoman court poetry, a student in Istanbul can also analyze the relationship of modern Turkish novels with <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turk-edebiyati-temel-eserler/" data-type="post" data-id="7356">Western literature</a>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="2-turkey-has-produced-world-famous-literary-figures">2. Turkey has produced world-famous literary figures</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey has been home to many world-renowned writers and poets in classical and contemporary literature. When you study language and literature in <strong>Turkey</strong>, you will have the opportunity to study the works of these literary figures in their own context.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📌 <strong>Famous Writers and Poets:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Yunus Emre (13th century):</strong> One of the most important figures of Turkish Sufi literature.</li>



<li><strong>Nazım Hikmet (20th century):</strong> A pioneer of modernism in Turkish poetry, a poet recognized worldwide.</li>



<li><strong>Orhan Pamuk (21st century):</strong> 2006 Nobel Prize winner for Literature, his works have been translated into more than 60 languages.</li>



<li><strong>Elif Şafak:</strong> One of the leading names in contemporary Turkish literature, her works are internationally acclaimed.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>While studying language and literature in Turkey, you will have the chance to analyze the works of these authors within an academic framework.</strong> You will also gain a better understanding of the historical, cultural and sociological contexts of literary works.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Example:</strong> A student studying at Boğaziçi University can analyze Orhan Pamuk&#8217;s novels in terms of postmodern narrative techniques.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="3-you-can-access-works-written-in-different-languages-in-turkey">3. You Can Access Works Written in Different Languages in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Language and literature education</strong> in Turkey is not limited to Turkish. You can access many works from the Ottoman period <strong>written in Arabic, Persian and Ottoman Turkish</strong> as academic resources.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📌 <strong>Diversity of Languages and Sources:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>In Ottoman Divan Literature, <strong>Arabic and Persian words were used extensively</strong>.</li>



<li>In the Tanzimat and Servet-i Fünun Periods, <strong>French literature was greatly influenced</strong> and translated works were produced.</li>



<li>In the modern period, contemporary Turkish literature developed, influenced by <strong>English, Russian and French works</strong>.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Example:</strong> A student studying at Ankara University can access the Ottoman archives and analyze historical documents directly in Ottoman Turkish.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="4-turkey-makes-literature-more-meaningful-with-its-historical-and-cultural-atmosphere">4. Turkey Makes Literature More Meaningful with Its Historical and Cultural Atmosphere</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When studying language and literature in Turkey, you don&#8217;t just learn from books. You can meet directly with literary circles through cultural events, book fairs, literary festivals and poetry nights organized in big cities like Istanbul, Ankara and Izmir.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📌 <strong>Cultural and Academic Activities:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Istanbul International Book Fair:</strong> Brings together authors and publishers from around the world.</li>



<li><strong>Nazım Hikmet Cultural Center:</strong> Poetry readings and literary panels are organized.</li>



<li><strong>Turkish Language Association Workshops:</strong> Events are organized with the participation of academics who are experts in linguistics and literature.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Example:</strong> A student studying at Istanbul University can gain new perspectives on their academic studies by meeting authors one-on-one at the Istanbul Book Fair.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📍 <strong>Recommended Universities:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Istanbul University</strong> &#8211; Turkish Language and Literature, Eastern Languages and Literatures</li>



<li><strong>Ankara University</strong> &#8211; Ottoman Turkish and Turkish Literature Studies</li>



<li><strong>Boğaziçi University</strong> &#8211; English Language and Literature</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="economic-and-quality-education">Economic and Quality Education</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">University education in Europe and the US can be quite expensive. However, studying language and literature in <strong>Turkey</strong> offers an affordable and high-quality academic experience.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>State Universities:</strong> Annual tuition fees range from <strong>300 &#8211; 1500 USD</strong>.</li>



<li><strong>Private Universities:</strong> Although the prices of private schools vary between <strong>5000 &#8211; 20,000 USD</strong>, scholarship opportunities are quite high.</li>



<li><strong>Turkey Scholarships:</strong> For successful international students, it offers full scholarships, accommodation and health insurance.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📍 <strong>Example:</strong> A student who wins a full scholarship under Turkey Scholarships can easily cover accommodation and basic living expenses with the monthly scholarship fee.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">👉 <strong><a href="https://www.turkiyeburslari.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click for detailed information about Turkey Scholarships!</a></strong></p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="universities-open-to-international-students">Universities Open to International Students</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey has a large number of programs for international students in languages such as <strong>English, French, Arabic and Russian</strong>. This is a great advantage for international students who want to study <strong>language and literature</strong> in Turkey.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Advantages:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>English education option:</strong> You can study in English at schools such as Boğaziçi University, <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/orta-dogu-teknik-universitesi-tanitim-rehberi/" data-type="page" data-id="350">Orta East Technical University (METU</a>) and Koç University.</li>



<li><strong>Erasmus and Mevlana Programs:</strong> You can participate in exchange programs at universities in Europe and Asia.</li>



<li><strong>Cultural Diversity on Campuses:</strong> You can interact with <strong>students from more than 150 countries</strong> studying at universities in Turkey.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📍 <strong>Recommended Universities:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Hacettepe University</strong> &#8211; English Translation and Interpreting</li>



<li><strong>Ege University</strong> &#8211; French and Spanish Literature</li>



<li><strong>Istanbul University</strong> &#8211; Russian Language and Literature</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="language-learning-opportunity">Language Learning Opportunity</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Studying in Turkey is a great opportunity to learn Turkish on the spot. You can also specialize in <strong>linguistics or translation</strong> by doing academic studies in languages such as Ottoman Turkish, Arabic and Persian.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>TÖMER Language Courses:</strong> One of the best institutions to learn Turkish before or during university studies in Turkey.</li>



<li><strong>Language Practice in Daily Life:</strong> You can quickly learn Turkish by practicing while shopping, in restaurants and on public transportation.</li>



<li><strong>Bilingual Education:</strong> You can learn a second or third language by studying English, French or Arabic in Turkey.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📍 <strong>Example:</strong> While studying at a university in Istanbul, you can quickly practice speaking Turkish by attending Turkish courses at <strong>TÖMER</strong> on weekends.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-best-universities-for-language-and-literature-programs-in-turkey">The Best Universities for Language and Literature Programs in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to study language and literature in Turkey, you can choose universities that stand out with their academic achievements and opportunities. Here are the best:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="1-bogazici-university-istanbul">1. Bogazici University (Istanbul)</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Departments:</strong> English Language and Literature, American Culture and Literature</li>



<li><strong>Signature:</strong> Full English language education, strong Erasmus program</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="2-hacettepe-university-ankara">2. Hacettepe University (Ankara)</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Departments:</strong> Linguistics, Contemporary Turkish Dialects, English Translation and Interpreting</li>



<li><strong>Feature:</strong> Academics specialized in language research</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="3-istanbul-university">3. Istanbul University</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Departments:</strong> Turkish Language and Literature, French Language and Literature, German Language and Literature</li>



<li><strong>Striking Feature:</strong> One of the oldest literature faculties in Turkey</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="4-ankara-university">4. Ankara University</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Departments:</strong> Arabic Language and Literature, Persian Language and Literature, Russian Language and Literature</li>



<li><strong>Striking Feature:</strong> Wide choice of languages, translation-oriented education</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="5-ege-university-izmir">5. Ege University (Izmir)</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Sciences:</strong> Spanish, Russian, Translation Studies</li>



<li><strong>Strong Feature:</strong> Multilingual academic research opportunities</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Visit <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">roadtostudy.com</a> to check out our detailed university guide!</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-process-and-admission-requirements">Application Process and Admission Requirements</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To apply to a language and literature program in Turkey, you must meet the following requirements:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>High School Diploma and GPA</strong><br>Most universities require a minimum GPA (usually 70/100 or equivalent).</li>



<li><strong>Language Proficiency Exam</strong></li>
</ol>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Turkish departments may require <strong><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-tomer-turkce-ogretim-merkezleri/" data-type="post" data-id="8067">TÖMER</a></strong> certificate.</li>



<li>For English programs, <strong>TOEFL or IELTS</strong> may be required.</li>
</ul>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>University Entrance Exam (YÖS or SAT)</strong><br>Some universities may require a <strong>Foreign National Student Exam (YÖS)</strong> or <strong>SAT</strong> score.</li>



<li><strong>Motivation Letter and References</strong><br>The motivation letter and academic reference are of great importance, especially in literature departments.</li>
</ol>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="career-opportunities-of-studying-language-and-literature-in-turkey">Career Opportunities of Studying Language and Literature in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Studying language and literature in Turkey</strong> offers not only academic knowledge but also a wide range of career opportunities. After graduation, you may have the opportunity to work in different fields from academics to translators, from publishing to teaching. So, <strong>In which job fields can language and literature graduates make a career in Turkey?</strong> Here are the details!</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="1-academics-academic-career-in-universities">1. Academics: Academic Career in Universities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you have studied language and literature in Turkey and want to advance in the academic world, you can pursue a career as a lecturer at universities. Academics is a profession that requires conducting research, publishing articles and mentoring students.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📌 <strong>How to Become an Academic?</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Get a Master&#8217;s and PhD:</strong> To become an academic, you usually need a Master&#8217;s and PhD.</li>



<li><strong>Start as a Research Assistant:</strong> Many universities in Turkey accept new graduates as research assistants.</li>



<li><strong>Participate in International Conferences:</strong> To be recognized in the academic world, you should publish international articles and participate in conferences.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Example:</strong> A student with a master&#8217;s degree at Istanbul University can start his academic career by doing a PhD on Ottoman literature.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="2-global-business-opportunities">2: Global Business Opportunities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>If you have studied languages and literature in Turkey</strong> and are fluent in more than one language, a career as a <strong>translator</strong> may be for you. Translation ranges from <strong>books to official documents, subtitles to technical texts</strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📌 <strong>Where you can work as a translator:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Literary Translation:</strong> You can translate novels, stories, poetry and academic works.</li>



<li><strong>Film and TV Series Translation:</strong> You can translate subtitles and dubbing for platforms such as Netflix and Amazon Prime.</li>



<li><strong>Official Documents and Legal Translation:</strong> You can translate passports, contracts and diplomatic documents.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Example:</strong> A student graduating in English Language and Literature in Turkey can work with international publishing houses to translate world-famous novels into Turkish.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="3-publishing-and-editing-work-in-the-book-and-media-world">3. Publishing and Editing: Work in the Book and Media World</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you studied language and literature in <strong>Turkey</strong> and love writing, <strong>publishing and editing</strong> is for you! </p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Book Editing:</strong> You can edit novels and academic books.</li>



<li><strong>Journalism and Column Writing:</strong> You can write for digital media or print newspapers.</li>



<li><strong>Content Production:</strong> You can do blogging, website content writing or social media management.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Example:</strong> A graduate working in the publishing industry in Turkey can work as an editor in a publishing house, checking the grammar and content of books.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="4th-language-teaching-become-a-turkish-or-foreign-language-teacher">4th Language Teaching: Become a Turkish or Foreign Language Teacher</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you enjoy teaching people languages, you can work as a <strong>teacher</strong> after graduation. You can teach <strong>Turkish language to foreign students</strong> in Turkey, or you can teach languages such as English, French, Russian in international schools.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">📌 <strong>Where You Can Work as a Language Teacher:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Public and Private Schools:</strong> You can work as a language teacher in primary schools, high schools and universities.</li>



<li><strong>Language Courses:</strong> You can teach Turkish at language centers like <strong>TÖMER</strong>.</li>



<li><strong>Private Lessons and Online Education:</strong> As a freelance teacher, you can earn income by giving private lessons.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Example:</strong> A student studying French in Turkey can work as a French teacher in an international school after graduation.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<h2 id="sonuç-turkiyede-dil-ve-edebiyat-egitimi-almak-mantikli-mi" class="wp-block-heading">Is it reasonable to study language and literature in Turkey?</h2>
<p>Absolutely yes! Turkey is a great option for international students due to its academic quality, affordable cost of living, and cultural diversity. You can also study economically thanks to Turkey Scholarships and other scholarship opportunities.</p>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">In which university is the best department of Turkish Language and Literature?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">According to the rankings and academic staff, the most prominent universities are Boğaziçi University (English), TOBB ETÜ (Scholarship) and the well-established state universities of Istanbul, Hacettepe, Ankara and <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/marmara-universitesi-tanitim-kampus-rehberi/" data-type="page" data-id="481">Marmara Universities</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="best-universities-for-language-department-in-turkey">Best universities for language department in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In general, language, translation and interpreting and teaching departments of universities such as METU, <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/yeditepe-universitesi/" data-type="page" data-id="860">Yeditepe</a>, Bahçeşehir, Hacettepe, <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/ted-universitesi-tanitimi/" data-type="page" data-id="1383">TED</a> are at the top with their academic quality and high base scores.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="where-to-study-turkish-language-and-literature">Where to study Turkish Language and Literature?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Established universities (e.g. Istanbul, Boğaziçi, Ankara, Ege) in major cities (Istanbul, Ankara, Izmir) are often recommended for their extensive library facilities, expert academic staff, and social environment.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="which-university-to-go-to-with-ydt">Which university to go to with YDT?</h3>



