d in studying agriculture and","name":"Agriculture and Agricultural Engineering Programs in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/agriculture-and-agricultural-engineering-programs/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/agriculture-and-agricultural-engineering-programs/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/agriculture-and-agricultural-engineering-programs.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/agriculture-and-agricultural-engineering-programs/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">With its vast agricultural areas and strong agricultural sector, Turkey is an excellent destination for students interested in studying agriculture and agricultural engineering. Thanks to modern agricultural techniques, sustainable production methods and the use of advanced technology, Turkey is rapidly developing in the field of agricultural education.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In this article, you will find everything you need to know about <strong>studying agriculture and agricultural engineering in Turkey</strong>: Top universities, application requirements, scholarships, costs and job opportunities!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">The Advantages of Studying Agricultural Engineering in Turkey</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">1. Turkey&#8217;s Agricultural Wealth and Diversity</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is one of the world&#8217;s most advantageous countries in terms of its agricultural sector. Due to the different climate zones found throughout the country, there is a wide variety of agricultural production. Many agricultural areas have developed in Turkey, such as crop production, animal husbandry, organic farming, and modern greenhouse systems.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="2nd-applied-and-technological-agriculture-training">2. Applied and Technological Agriculture Training</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey&#8217;s agricultural engineering and agricultural faculties offer students not only theoretical knowledge but also practical training. Farm internships, agricultural research laboratories and field trips give students the opportunity to gain practical experience in the industry. Modern topics such as digital agriculture, smart irrigation systems and biotechnology are also included in the curriculum.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="3-affordable-university-education">3. Affordable University Education</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Agricultural and agricultural engineering education in Turkey is much more affordable than in Europe and the US. Annual tuition fees, especially at public universities, range from 300 &#8211; 1,000 USD. At foundation universities, the cost of education may be slightly higher, but these universities offer scholarships to international students.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="4th-global-career-and-business-opportunities">4. Global Career and Business Opportunities</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are job opportunities for agriculture and agricultural engineering graduates not only in Turkey but also around the world. Students specializing in areas such as food production, ecological agriculture, irrigation engineering, agricultural technology and animal husbandry can find jobs in international agricultural companies, government agencies and global food organizations.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="5-scholarship-opportunities-for-international-students">5. Scholarship Opportunities for International Students</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey offers various scholarship programs for international students. Turkey Scholarships provide students with full scholarships, accommodation and monthly allowance, while some private universities also offer scholarships based on academic achievement.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="advantages-of-studying-agriculture-and-agricultural-engineering-in-turkey">Advantages of Studying Agriculture and Agricultural Engineering in Turkey</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th>Advantage</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Turkey’s Agricultural Diversity</strong></td><td>Thanks to its varied climate conditions, Turkey offers vast agricultural lands and a wide range of plant and animal production options.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Hands-On Agricultural Education</strong></td><td>Education includes laboratory work, farm visits, agricultural projects, and training in modern farming technologies.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Affordable University Fees</strong></td><td>Annual tuition fees at public universities range from <strong>300 to 1,000 USD</strong>, while private universities offer various scholarship opportunities.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Global Career Opportunities</strong></td><td>Agricultural engineering graduates can work in international companies, government institutions, and agricultural research centers.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Scholarships for International Students</strong></td><td>Türkiye Scholarships and private foundation grants provide full funding for education and living expenses.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Studying <strong>agricultural and agricultural engineering</strong> in Turkey provides you with <strong>quality education and global job opportunities</strong>. If you are interested in studying <strong>agricultural and agricultural engineering</strong> in Turkey, please contact us via <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Road to Study</a> for more information about the application process and scholarship opportunities!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">The Best Universities Offering Agricultural Engineering Education in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many high-quality university options for international students wishing to pursue agricultural and agricultural engineering education in Turkey. Turkey offers extensive academic opportunities for students seeking to specialize in areas such as plant production, agricultural biotechnology, irrigation engineering, ecological agriculture, and modern agricultural technologies.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Below, we detail the best universities offering agricultural and agricultural engineering education and the prominent agricultural specialization areas at these universities:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th>University</th><th>City</th><th>Key Focus Areas</th><th>Language of Instruction</th><th>Estimated Annual Tuition (USD)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Ankara University</strong></td><td>Ankara</td><td>Plant production, agricultural biotechnology, agricultural economics</td><td>Turkish, English</td><td>300 – 1,000 (Public)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Ege University</strong></td><td>İzmir</td><td>Ecological farming, agricultural mechanization, organic agriculture</td><td>Turkish</td><td>300 – 1,000 (Public)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Çukurova University</strong></td><td>Adana</td><td>Irrigation systems, warm-climate agriculture, greenhouse cultivation</td><td>Turkish, English</td><td>300 – 1,000 (Public)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Selçuk University</strong></td><td>Konya</td><td>Traditional and modern farming techniques, livestock engineering</td><td>Turkish</td><td>300 – 1,000 (Public)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Akdeniz University</strong></td><td>Antalya</td><td>Tropical agriculture, greenhouse systems, smart farming technologies</td><td>Turkish, English</td><td>300 – 1,000 (Public)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Ondokuz Mayıs University</strong></td><td>Samsun</td><td>Agricultural biotechnology, water management, fruit growing</td><td>Turkish</td><td>300 – 1,000 (Public)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Atatürk University</strong></td><td>Erzurum</td><td>Cold-climate farming, soil sciences, animal nutrition</td><td>Turkish</td><td>300 – 1,000 (Public)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Istanbul University – Cerrahpaşa</strong></td><td>Istanbul</td><td>Agricultural biotechnology, plant protection, food engineering</td><td>Turkish, English</td><td>500 – 2,000 (Public)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Bursa Uludağ University</strong></td><td>Bursa</td><td>Sustainable agriculture, fruit and vegetable cultivation</td><td>Turkish</td><td>300 – 1,000 (Public)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Note:</strong> Foundation (private) universities may have higher fees (3,000 &#8211; 10,000 USD), but there are scholarship options for international students.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-requirements-for-agriculture-and-agricultural-engineering-programs-in-turkey">Application Requirements for Agriculture and Agricultural Engineering Programs in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The general application requirements for international students who wish to study agricultural engineering in Turkey are as follows:</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="1-high-school-diploma-and-academic-requirements">1. High School Diploma and Academic Requirements</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the most important requirements to apply to agricultural engineering programs in Turkey is to have a <strong>high school diploma</strong>.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Diploma must be in a field related to science, engineering, biology or agriculture.</li>



<li>Some universities may require a <strong>minimum grade point average (GPA)</strong> in certain subjects on high school transcripts. For example, high grades in math, biology and chemistry can be an advantage.</li>



<li><strong>Notarized</strong> or <strong>apostilled</strong> high school diploma is required. (You must have it approved before coming to Turkey.)</li>



<li>As the language of instruction in Turkey is English or Turkish, a <strong>Turkish or English translation</strong> of the diploma may also be required.</li>
</ul>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="2-requirements-for-english-and-turkish-programs">2: Requirements for English and Turkish Programs</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Agricultural engineering education in Turkey is offered in <strong>Turkish or English</strong>. Depending on the language of instruction at the university, you may be required to take one of the following language exams:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th><strong>Program Language</strong></th>
<th><strong>Required Language Exam</strong></th>
<th><strong>Minimum Score</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Turkish</strong></td>
<td>Turkish Proficiency Exam (TÖMER)</td>
<td>B2 or above</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>English</strong></td>
<td>TOEFL IBT</td>
<td>70-80+</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>If you want to study in Turkish programs, you need to pass the <strong>TÖMER exam</strong>. If you don&#8217;t speak Turkish, some universities offer <strong>1 year of preparatory education</strong>.</li>



<li>If you want to study in English and do not have enough points, you can join the university&#8217;s <strong>English preparatory program</strong>.</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="3-pds-sat-and-others">3: PDS, SAT and Others</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Many universities in Turkey require <strong>university entrance exam</strong> scores from international students. Accepted exams are:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table"><br /><strong>SAT (Scholastic Aptitude Test)</strong>U.S.-based international examSome foundation and public universities</figure>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Exam Name</th>
<th>Description</th>
<th>Accepted By</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>YÖS (Foreign Student Exam)</strong></td>
<td>A special entrance exam organized by Turkish universities for international students</td>
<td>Most public universities</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>SAT (Scholastic Aptitude Test)</strong></td>
<td>A U.S.-based international standardized test used for university admissions</td>
<td>Some foundation and public universities</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>University-Specific Exams</strong></td>
<td>Entrance exams conducted individually by universities</td>
<td>Both public and private universities</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Admission Based on International Diplomas</strong></td>
<td>Students can be admitted with diplomas such as IB, A-Level, Abitur, or WAEC</td>
<td>Private and foundation universities</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-you-need-to-know-about-the-yos-exam">What You Need to Know About the YÖS Exam:</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>YÖS is an exam conducted by universities in Turkey for foreign students.</li>



<li>It usually consists of <strong>Mathematics and Logic Questions</strong>.</li>



<li>The exam is conducted in <strong>Turkish, English and sometimes Arabic</strong>.</li>



<li>YÖS score should be between <strong>50-90 out of 100</strong> depending on the university.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Universities Requiring SAT Score:</strong><br>Some foundation universities may accept applications with <strong>SAT score</strong>. Minimum SAT score generally required:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Math:</strong> 600+</li>



<li><strong>Total Score:</strong> 1100+</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="4-reference-and-motivation-letter">4. Reference and Motivation Letter</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some universities may require <strong>reference letters</strong> and <strong>motivation letters</strong> when evaluating your application.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tips-for-a-motivational-letter">Tips for a Motivational Letter:</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Explain why you want to study agricultural engineering in Turkey.</strong></li>



<li><strong>Indicate in which areas you would like to specialize </strong> (For example: Organic farming, agricultural technology, ecological farming, etc.)</li>



<li><strong>Describe your career goals.</strong></li>



<li><strong>Share your previous experiences and successes.</strong></li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tips-for-a-reference-letter">Tips for a Reference Letter:</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>You can ask your high school teachers or, if you have worked on agriculture-related projects, your managers.</li>



<li>The letter should be in <strong>English or Turkish</strong>.</li>



<li>A letter describing your academic achievements and character.</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="5-application-process-and-documents">5. Application Process and Documents</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applications can be submitted <strong>online</strong> or, at some universities, <strong>by mail</strong>. The following documents are usually requested at the time of application:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>High School Diploma</strong> (Apostilled and notarized)</li>



<li><strong>High School Transcript</strong> (Document showing your grade point average)</li>



<li><strong>Language Proficiency Certificate</strong> (TOEFL, IELTS or TÖMER certificate)</li>



<li><strong>Exam Results</strong> (YÖS, SAT or university exam)</li>



<li><strong>Passport Photocopy</strong></li>



<li><strong>Motivational Letter</strong> (if required)</li>



<li><strong>Reference Letter</strong> (If required)</li>



<li><strong><strong>Application Fee Receipt</strong> (30-150 USD depending on the university)</strong></li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Application deadlines <strong>vary from university to university</strong>, but in general:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>State Universities:</strong> April &#8211; July</li>



<li><strong>Foundation Universities:</strong> February &#8211; September</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For applications and detailed information, please contact us via <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Road to Study</a>!</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="cost-of-agriculture-and-agricultural-engineering-education-in-turkey-and-scholarships">Cost of Agriculture and Agricultural Engineering Education in Turkey and Scholarships</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The cost of a university education in Turkey varies between public and foundation universities.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th>Program Language</th><th>Required Language Exam</th><th>Minimum Score</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Turkish</strong></td><td>Turkish Proficiency Exam (TÖMER)</td><td>B2 or higher</td></tr><tr><td><strong>English</strong></td><td>TOEFL iBT</td><td>70–80+</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="scholarship-opportunities">Scholarship Opportunities</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong><a href="https://www.turkiyeburslari.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Turkey Scholarships</a>:</strong> Offers full scholarships for education and living expenses.</li>



<li><strong>University Scholarships:</strong> Scholarships are available based on academic achievement or financial need.</li>



<li><strong>Private Organizations:</strong> Foundations and associations provide scholarships for the agricultural sector.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Check out the <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Road to Study</a> scholarship guide to explore more scholarship options!</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="job-opportunities-for-agriculture-and-agricultural-engineering-graduates-in-turkey">Job Opportunities for Agriculture and Agricultural Engineering Graduates in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many job opportunities for agricultural engineering graduates in Turkey:</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="1-job-opportunities-in-state-institutions">1. Job Opportunities in State Institutions</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the most important job opportunities for graduates of <strong>agricultural and agricultural engineering and agricultural engineering</strong> in Turkey is in government agencies. The state employs agricultural engineers within different ministries and public organizations to support agricultural production, guide farmers and promote modern agricultural techniques.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="state-institutions-to-work-for">State Institutions to Work for:</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th>Institution</th><th>Main Responsibilities</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry</strong></td><td>Agricultural policies, food safety, and farmer support programs</td></tr><tr><td><strong>State Hydraulic Works (DSİ)</strong></td><td>Irrigation projects and agricultural water management</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Turkish Grain Board (TMO)</strong></td><td>Grain production, distribution, and food security management</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Municipalities and Agricultural Directorates</strong></td><td>Local agricultural initiatives and rural development projects</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Agricultural Credit Cooperatives</strong></td><td>Providing financial support and agricultural consultancy services to farmers</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="2-agriculture-and-food-industry-business-opportunities-in-the-private-sector">2. Agriculture and Food Industry Business Opportunities in the Private Sector</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The private sector is one of the areas that offers the most job opportunities for graduates of <strong>agricultural and agricultural engineering.</strong> Especially agricultural production, food industry and agricultural technologies sectors are developing rapidly.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="areas-of-employment-in-agriculture-and-food-sector">Areas of Employment in Agriculture and Food Sector:</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th>Sector</th><th>Fields of Work</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Agricultural Production Companies</strong></td><td>Greenhouse farming, livestock breeding, organic agriculture, and crop production</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Food Production and Processing Plants</strong></td><td>Flour, sugar, dairy, and fruit-vegetable processing facilities</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Agricultural Technology and Equipment Manufacturers</strong></td><td>Smart irrigation systems, agricultural drones, and biotechnology innovations</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Fertilizer and Seed Companies</strong></td><td>Organic fertilizers and genetically improved seed production</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Agrochemical Companies</strong></td><td>Pesticides, herbicides, and biological pest control methods</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>


<p> </p>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="3-research-and-academic-career-opportunities">3. Research and Academic Career Opportunities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Another job opportunity for agriculturaland agricultural engineering graduates is in academia. Working at universities or agricultural research institutes, you can work on topics such as agricultural innovation, biotechnology, sustainable agriculture and climate change adaptation.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="academic-and-research-institutions-to-work-at">Academic and Research Institutions to work at:</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Universities:</strong> You can work as an academic staff or researcher in agricultural engineering faculties.</li>



<li><strong>Agricultural Research Institutes:</strong> You can work as a researcher in state or private agricultural institutes.</li>



<li><strong>Private R&amp;D Centers:</strong> You can work in agricultural technology and biotechnology companies to develop innovative agricultural products and sustainable solutions.</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="4-international-organizations-and-global-business-opportunities">4. International Organizations and Global Business Opportunities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Agricultural engineering is a profession that offers job opportunities not only in Turkey but also <strong>internationally</strong>. <strong>Many organizations concerned with agriculture and food security around the world provide employment for agricultural engineers.</strong></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="international-organizations-and-fields-to-work-in">International Organizations and Fields to Work in:</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th>Organization</th><th>Related Fields</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>FAO (Food and Agriculture Organization)</strong></td><td>Sustainable agricultural policies and food security projects</td></tr><tr><td><strong>World Bank Agricultural Projects</strong></td><td>Rural development and agricultural growth support programs</td></tr><tr><td><strong>European Union Agricultural Programs</strong></td><td>Organic farming initiatives and agricultural support funds</td></tr><tr><td><strong>United Nations Development Programme (UNDP)</strong></td><td>Agricultural sustainability and water management projects</td></tr><tr><td><strong>International Agricultural Companies (Bayer, Syngenta, John Deere, etc.)</strong></td><td>Agricultural technologies and biotechnology</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">What are Agricultural Engineering programs?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Covers specialties such as Horticulture, Field Crops, Plant Protection, Animal Science, Agricultural Biotechnology, Soil Science and Agricultural Economics.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="in-which-universities-are-there-agricultural-engineering-departments">In which universities are there Agricultural Engineering departments?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are Faculties of Agriculture in many universities across Turkey. For example, there are programs at Akdeniz, Ege and Bilecik Şeyh Edebali University.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="which-is-the-best-agricultural-faculty-in-turkey">Which is the best agricultural faculty in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">According to the 2024 YKS, Mediterranean University Faculty of Agriculture ranked first in Turkey in some departments and became the most preferred faculty.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">How much does an agricultural engineer earn?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The average monthly salary for 2025 is approximately 58.300 TL, the lowest Agricultural Engineer salary is 46.600 TL and the highest is 151.100 TL.</p>



