<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The cost of a university education in Turkey varies between public and foundation universities.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th>Program Language</th><th>Required Language Exam</th><th>Minimum Score</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Turkish</strong></td><td>Turkish Proficiency Exam (TÖMER)</td><td>B2 or higher</td></tr><tr><td><strong>English</strong></td><td>TOEFL iBT</td><td>70–80+</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="scholarship-opportunities">Scholarship Opportunities</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong><a href="https://www.turkiyeburslari.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Turkey Scholarships</a>:</strong> Offers full scholarships for education and living expenses.</li>



<li><strong>University Scholarships:</strong> Scholarships are available based on academic achievement or financial need.</li>



<li><strong>Private Organizations:</strong> Foundations and associations provide scholarships for the agricultural sector.</li>
</ul>



