<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="5-post-graduation-career-opportunities">5. Post-Graduation Career Opportunities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many job opportunities for Aerospace Engineering graduates in Turkey and around the world:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Aviation Companies</strong>: You can work as an engineer in companies such as THY, Pegasus, TAI.</li>



<li><strong>Space and Defense Industry</strong>: You can take part in space technologies and defense projects in companies such as ASELSAN, ROKETSAN, HAVELSAN.</li>



<li><strong>Research and Academia</strong>: You can pursue an academic career at universities or work in private research centers.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="does-it-make-sense-to-study-aerospace-engineering-in-turkey">Does it make sense to study Aerospace Engineering in Turkey?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are interested in technology and want to pursue a career in the aerospace industry, studying Aerospace Engineering in Turkey is a great option! Turkey offers great opportunities in this field with its developing space and defense industry, strong academic programs and international job opportunities.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For the application process and detailed guide, please visit <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">roadtostudy.com</a>!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Aerospace Engineering education in Turkey is available at well-established universities, particularly Istanbul Technical University (ITU) and Middle East Technical University (METU).</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">In which university to study Aerospace Engineering?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Principally METU and ITU, Eskişehir Technical, <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/gebze-teknik-universitesi-tanitim-rehberi/" data-type="page" data-id="511">Gebze Technical</a> and Turkish Aeronautical Association Universities are the leading institutions in this field. It is also available at many other state and foundation universities.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">How much does an aerospace engineer earn?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Salaries for aerospace engineers vary according to experience and the organization they work for, but according to 2025 data, the average monthly salary is around <strong>139,800 TL</strong>; the highest salaries can go up to 230,500 TL.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="aircraft-engineering-best-universities-in-turkey">Aircraft engineering best universities in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The best universities in Turkey for Aeronautical Engineering are Istanbul Technical University (ITU), Turkish Aeronautical Association University and Gebze Technical University. Success rankings usually point to these institutions.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-there-a-clear-path-for-aerospace-engineering">Is there a clear path for aerospace engineering?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, the way forward is open. Especially in Turkey, career opportunities in both the public and private sectors are increasing rapidly thanks to intensive investments in the defense industry, aviation projects and space technologies.</p>



